1
00:00:06,027 --> 00:00:08,946
-[keys jangling]
-[lock clicking]

2
00:00:09,030 --> 00:00:11,115
[gate creaking]

3
00:00:11,198 --> 00:00:12,575
[light switch clicking]

4
00:00:12,658 --> 00:00:16,454
["Rest (Gönder Gelsin)" by Ramiz playing]

5
00:00:19,457 --> 00:00:21,208
[engine running]

6
00:00:42,897 --> 00:00:43,898
[cup skittering]

7
00:00:52,948 --> 00:00:54,408
-[door squeaking]
-[thud]

8
00:00:56,202 --> 00:00:57,369
[doors slamming]

9
00:00:57,453 --> 00:00:58,996
[music continues]

10
00:01:10,633 --> 00:01:11,592
[drink splashing]

11
00:01:13,427 --> 00:01:16,013
GOOD NIGHT, YASEMIN.
I'M THINKING ABOUT YOU.

12
00:01:26,273 --> 00:01:29,318
Excuse me, we have to close.
Can I take you outside?

13
00:01:29,902 --> 00:01:31,112
[Yusuf] Come on, let's go.

14
00:01:38,869 --> 00:01:40,496
[keys beeping]

15
00:01:43,415 --> 00:01:44,416
[Ivan] Yusuf.

16
00:01:46,585 --> 00:01:48,170
[money rustling]

17
00:01:51,006 --> 00:01:52,007
Attaboy.

18
00:01:53,342 --> 00:01:54,343
[Ivan scoffs]

19
00:01:55,970 --> 00:01:57,221
[door opens]

20
00:02:01,016 --> 00:02:01,976
[music ends]

21
00:02:02,059 --> 00:02:03,352
[loud clang]

22
00:02:04,311 --> 00:02:06,021
-[doorbell chimes]
-[Yusuf exhales]

23
00:02:07,022 --> 00:02:08,566
[card rustling]

24
00:02:12,653 --> 00:02:14,405
[opening theme music playing]

25
00:02:19,118 --> 00:02:20,244
[music ends]

26
00:02:20,327 --> 00:02:22,496
[muffled voice]
I was looking for the bear.

27
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:25,082
I was looking for it… for weeks.

28
00:02:25,791 --> 00:02:26,750
[Max] Hey, babe?

29
00:02:27,626 --> 00:02:28,586
Yeah.

30
00:02:28,669 --> 00:02:29,795
[Max] You got company.

31
00:02:31,046 --> 00:02:32,173
What?

32
00:02:32,256 --> 00:02:35,217
[Andrei] As soon as I got out of the bush,
he started running away from me.

33
00:02:35,301 --> 00:02:38,053
-[Max] What'd you do?
-[Andrei] I… I got my skis…

34
00:02:38,137 --> 00:02:39,263
-[Max] Hey.
-[Morgan] Hey. Hi.

35
00:02:39,346 --> 00:02:41,473
Did you forget you had
a meeting with Chuck and…

36
00:02:41,557 --> 00:02:43,559
-Lenny.
-Yes. Lenny.

37
00:02:44,810 --> 00:02:45,811
Um…

38
00:02:48,063 --> 00:02:49,773
Yeah, I forgot to mention

39
00:02:50,733 --> 00:02:53,319
these guys run
the summer school program. [gulps]

40
00:02:53,402 --> 00:02:55,821
And I keep telling them
I'm not interested.

41
00:02:55,905 --> 00:02:58,949
[Max] Yeah. Morgan, these guys
are fucking badass.

42
00:02:59,033 --> 00:03:01,118
Lenny was just telling me
how back in Russia,

43
00:03:01,202 --> 00:03:02,953
he used to, like, hunt for his own dinner

44
00:03:03,037 --> 00:03:05,039
with his bare hands.

45
00:03:05,122 --> 00:03:06,373
[Morgan] Um, babe…

46
00:03:07,166 --> 00:03:10,878
[smacks lips] Would you maybe mind
grabbing a couple coffees for everyone?

47
00:03:11,378 --> 00:03:12,546
Yeah, for sure. I'm just--

48
00:03:12,630 --> 00:03:15,925
I'm kind of in the middle of toasting
an egg everything for Chuck right now.

49
00:03:16,008 --> 00:03:18,010
Chuck, okay. I can handle that.

50
00:03:18,093 --> 00:03:19,220
-[Max] Yeah?
-Yeah.

51
00:03:19,303 --> 00:03:20,387
-Okay.
-Yeah, yeah, yeah.

52
00:03:20,471 --> 00:03:22,973
-Sure. Yeah.
-Thank you, I appreciate you.

53
00:03:23,057 --> 00:03:24,850
-[Max] You boys take it black?
-[keys jangling]

54
00:03:24,934 --> 00:03:27,603
Frappuccino with caramel squirt.

55
00:03:28,771 --> 00:03:29,772
[door closes]

56
00:03:29,855 --> 00:03:33,192
Okay, um… You guys need
to get the fuck out of my house.

57
00:03:33,275 --> 00:03:37,404
You can tell a lot
by what someone chooses to frame.

58
00:03:37,488 --> 00:03:40,282
All the people they'd be scared to lose.

59
00:03:40,366 --> 00:03:41,533
[toaster pops loudly]

60
00:03:41,617 --> 00:03:44,119
[Ivan] We've been impressed
with your work, Morgan.

61
00:03:44,203 --> 00:03:45,287
Thank you.

62
00:03:47,248 --> 00:03:48,123
[floor squeaks]

63
00:03:48,207 --> 00:03:53,379
We need you to accompany Yusuf
to finish a job, an important one.

64
00:03:53,462 --> 00:03:57,383
Months of planning. It cannot fail.
I mean, if it fails--

65
00:03:57,466 --> 00:03:59,009
[Andrei] Deadly, very bad.

66
00:03:59,093 --> 00:04:01,845
-I get your point. I'll talk to Nicky.
-[Ivan] Uh-uh-uh.

67
00:04:01,929 --> 00:04:05,140
We're having reservations
about your brother.

68
00:04:05,224 --> 00:04:06,475
Reservations?

69
00:04:06,558 --> 00:04:07,518
He's scaredy-cat.

70
00:04:07,601 --> 00:04:10,354
-He's not of value to us.
-[butters toast]

71
00:04:10,437 --> 00:04:13,732
[Ivan] He's proved to be a liability.

72
00:04:15,234 --> 00:04:17,069
What does that mean? What does that mean?

73
00:04:17,152 --> 00:04:20,990
Like, I understand that he's not, like,
a great hang or fun or anything like that,

74
00:04:21,073 --> 00:04:22,074
but… but he's not a li--

75
00:04:22,157 --> 00:04:23,867
[inhales deeply] He's not a liability.

76
00:04:23,951 --> 00:04:26,036
You bet your life on this?

77
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:29,540
Because if anything goes wrong,

78
00:04:29,623 --> 00:04:31,875
all of this will be on you,
you know. [exhales]

79
00:04:31,959 --> 00:04:33,877
-[Morgan] Hmm.
-[Ivan inhales]

80
00:04:33,961 --> 00:04:36,380
Lady, you got an ashtray?

81
00:04:36,463 --> 00:04:39,758
[Nicky] I'm so sorry
I slept through our meeting, Rose.

82
00:04:39,842 --> 00:04:43,679
My alarm didn't go off,
and it's never happened before. I'm…

83
00:04:43,762 --> 00:04:47,182
Can I get you a tea
or a coffee or something?

84
00:04:47,266 --> 00:04:50,060
I'm fine. I think you should sit down.

85
00:04:50,144 --> 00:04:51,895
If this is about the fall festival budget,

86
00:04:51,979 --> 00:04:55,024
I will get my approvals in
like top of next week, I promise.

87
00:04:55,107 --> 00:04:56,066
[Rose] Of course.

88
00:04:56,817 --> 00:04:58,235
Is everything all right?

89
00:04:58,819 --> 00:05:00,821
Yeah, everything's fine. Why… Why?

90
00:05:01,322 --> 00:05:05,701
Well, we've received
some constructive criticism

91
00:05:05,784 --> 00:05:07,328
from the congregation.

92
00:05:07,828 --> 00:05:09,455
Well, okay. What about?

93
00:05:09,538 --> 00:05:13,417
[Rose] I'm wondering if "we"
was the right choice of word.

94
00:05:14,001 --> 00:05:15,461
It's more about you.

95
00:05:16,045 --> 00:05:17,921
What are people saying, Rose?

96
00:05:18,005 --> 00:05:20,257
Well… Uh… [clears throat]

97
00:05:20,341 --> 00:05:23,427
Just a few notes
about some recent sermons. [inhales]

98
00:05:23,510 --> 00:05:25,054
"A tad meandering."

99
00:05:26,347 --> 00:05:28,557
"I did not like this."

100
00:05:29,475 --> 00:05:34,438
Oh, and, "Preferred my recent experience
at the DMV."

101
00:05:34,521 --> 00:05:36,273
Um… [scoffs]

102
00:05:36,357 --> 00:05:39,526
Well, I… I can spend more time on them.

103
00:05:39,610 --> 00:05:43,113
-"Unreliable. Distracted."
-[Nicky sighs]

104
00:05:43,197 --> 00:05:44,573
"Like a ghost."

105
00:05:44,656 --> 00:05:45,741
Nobody wrote that.

106
00:05:45,824 --> 00:05:49,036
I know your grandmother's death
was very hard on you,

107
00:05:49,119 --> 00:05:52,456
but we have Mary McCutcheon's
parents' memorial tomorrow,

108
00:05:52,539 --> 00:05:55,250
and you know she wanted
to meet with you today.

109
00:05:55,334 --> 00:05:56,460
I know… I know that.

110
00:05:56,543 --> 00:05:59,838
I'd be happy to handle it
if you want to take some time off.

111
00:05:59,922 --> 00:06:03,592
Rose, I am… I am more than capable
of… of handling this, okay?

112
00:06:03,675 --> 00:06:07,304
I don't need to take time off.
I just need more hours in a day

113
00:06:07,388 --> 00:06:12,059
and a mic that doesn't cack out halfway
through my apparently agonizing sermons.

114
00:06:12,142 --> 00:06:16,438
[inhales] This congregation
is my top priority.

115
00:06:17,272 --> 00:06:19,358
[cell phone ringing]

116
00:06:23,612 --> 00:06:25,697
-[ringing continues]
-[Nicky clears throat]

117
00:06:25,781 --> 00:06:28,325
-Do you need to get that?
-I need to get that. I need to get that.

118
00:06:28,409 --> 00:06:31,412
But this has nothing to do
with me being distracted, okay?

119
00:06:32,329 --> 00:06:34,498
[Natalie gasps] You're kidding me.

120
00:06:35,541 --> 00:06:37,376
[whispers] Three prostitutes…

121
00:06:38,377 --> 00:06:41,088
-[gasps] Uh-huh. On Tom's yacht.
-[whispers] No!

122
00:06:41,171 --> 00:06:42,297
[Linda gasps]

123
00:06:42,381 --> 00:06:44,133
-Bra and panties.
-Oh my…

124
00:06:44,216 --> 00:06:46,844
-Uh-- Not on the prostitutes.
-[Linda gasps]

125
00:06:46,927 --> 00:06:49,221
[chuckles] Okay. They're called
sex workers. I have to go.

126
00:06:49,304 --> 00:06:51,056
Nat, it's karma. It's karma!

127
00:06:51,140 --> 00:06:52,558
-Mom?
-What does it mean?

128
00:06:52,641 --> 00:06:54,059
Do you think he'll be dropping out?

129
00:06:54,143 --> 00:06:56,937
Ugh. When your constituency is
God-fearing country clubbers,

130
00:06:57,020 --> 00:06:59,523
I don't think playing dress-up
with sex workers is a good look.

131
00:06:59,606 --> 00:07:01,400
Well, what happens now?

132
00:07:01,483 --> 00:07:05,904
Well, I don't see how you can lose
a race if you're the only one running.

133
00:07:06,905 --> 00:07:08,782
[Linda breathes deeply]

134
00:07:08,866 --> 00:07:11,243
Holy shit, Natalie.

135
00:07:11,326 --> 00:07:12,369
I know, I know, I know!

136
00:07:12,453 --> 00:07:15,706
I don't think we should jump to any
conclusions at this point, but I know.

137
00:07:15,789 --> 00:07:17,124
I just… [voice breaking]

138
00:07:18,125 --> 00:07:20,252
-Yeah.
-[whispers] Sixty-five years old.

139
00:07:20,335 --> 00:07:22,337
-Never finished college.
-…finished college. I know.

140
00:07:22,421 --> 00:07:24,756
-Gave birth to you during that blizzard.
-…blizzard. I know.

141
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,842
-[sobs] Oh God!
-You have come a long way, Mom.

142
00:07:26,925 --> 00:07:28,844
-I think of that Facebook group…
-Yeah.

143
00:07:28,927 --> 00:07:32,306
…and how supportive they were
when I announced that I was running.

144
00:07:32,389 --> 00:07:35,976
Half of them have Tom Donaldson signs
in their front yards.

145
00:07:36,059 --> 00:07:38,812
Susan Gopnik joked to her mah-jongg group

146
00:07:38,896 --> 00:07:43,358
that I must have been having a stroke
when I decided to run.

147
00:07:43,442 --> 00:07:47,863
-So who's stroking now? [laughs]
-[Natalie laughing] Yeah!

148
00:07:47,946 --> 00:07:49,490
[both screaming, laughing]

149
00:07:49,573 --> 00:07:52,493
-I'm gonna post that.
-No. No, no, we don't need to post that.

150
00:07:52,576 --> 00:07:54,286
-[Natalie] Yay!
-[both laughing]

151
00:07:54,369 --> 00:07:55,913
[funky music playing]

152
00:07:56,413 --> 00:07:57,706
[cars whooshing by]

153
00:07:58,332 --> 00:07:59,374
[music ends]

154
00:07:59,458 --> 00:08:02,461
Yeah, I am so sorry
I wasn't able to be there today, Mary,

155
00:08:02,544 --> 00:08:06,381
but tomorrow's gonna be a lovely
celebration of life for your parents.

156
00:08:06,882 --> 00:08:10,427
I did-- I got the email,
and I got your remarks.

157
00:08:10,511 --> 00:08:13,597
No, I think it's great.
I mean, I have a few small thoughts.

158
00:08:13,680 --> 00:08:16,475
You know, I'm just not sure your friends
and family need to be reminded

159
00:08:16,558 --> 00:08:18,477
of the grislier details of the crash.

160
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:19,436
[car honking]

161
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:21,813
Do you know what I'm saying? I… Right.

162
00:08:21,897 --> 00:08:23,941
I just think words like "decapitation"

163
00:08:24,024 --> 00:08:26,735
might, you know, might not be
in the spirit of the day.

164
00:08:27,444 --> 00:08:31,573
Exactly, and I would remove
"charred" as well. "Charred."

165
00:08:31,657 --> 00:08:33,659
[Turkish hip-hop music playing]

166
00:08:33,742 --> 00:08:37,079
-[Yusuf raises volume]
-[Morgan lowers volume]

167
00:08:38,247 --> 00:08:39,915
What are we listening to?

168
00:08:39,998 --> 00:08:40,958
Music.

169
00:08:41,625 --> 00:08:42,918
Okay, if you say so.

170
00:08:43,001 --> 00:08:44,211
[Nicky speaking outside]

171
00:08:44,294 --> 00:08:46,338
All right, what is this today?

172
00:08:46,421 --> 00:08:50,425
It's like ranching licenses,
livestock permits.

173
00:08:51,051 --> 00:08:54,304
What are we walking into, it's like
a cockfighting ring, horse doping?

174
00:08:54,388 --> 00:08:56,848
Why is it only ever men
that get involved in this shit?

175
00:08:56,932 --> 00:08:58,976
[exhales] It's not for you
to worry about. Leave it.

176
00:08:59,059 --> 00:09:01,728
It kinda is, okay?
Now that we're on the same level,

177
00:09:01,812 --> 00:09:04,106
you can't just boss us around
all the time.

178
00:09:04,189 --> 00:09:06,775
What the fuck?
We are not on the same level.

179
00:09:07,526 --> 00:09:11,488
One of us knows what we are doing,
and two of us obviously don't.

180
00:09:11,572 --> 00:09:12,406
Oh.

181
00:09:12,489 --> 00:09:15,909
[inhales] If I got up right now,
walked out of this car,

182
00:09:15,993 --> 00:09:17,202
you'd be fucked.

183
00:09:17,286 --> 00:09:18,829
You would be fucked.

184
00:09:19,413 --> 00:09:22,874
I would be… Yeah, I would be fucked,
but you would be more fucked.

185
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:27,004
[scoffs] Well, listen, I've been doing
this job long before you,

186
00:09:27,087 --> 00:09:30,007
okay, and I'll be doing it
long after you're gone.

187
00:09:30,090 --> 00:09:31,216
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

188
00:09:31,300 --> 00:09:32,509
-You sure?
-Mm-hmm.

189
00:09:32,593 --> 00:09:36,805
[smacks lips] Because, um, Ivan said
that the reason both of us are here

190
00:09:36,888 --> 00:09:39,891
is because he doesn't trust you
to handle this on your own.

191
00:09:39,975 --> 00:09:40,934
[scoffs]

192
00:09:41,435 --> 00:09:43,437
-He didn't say that.
-Yeah, he did.

193
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,731
He did say that this morning,
sitting at my kitchen table

194
00:09:45,814 --> 00:09:47,065
eating an everything bagel.

195
00:09:47,149 --> 00:09:49,735
So, it kinda seems like
I'm here to babysit you guys, okay?

196
00:09:49,818 --> 00:09:52,195
Let that sink in, dick.

197
00:09:52,279 --> 00:09:53,864
[music continues]

198
00:09:53,947 --> 00:09:57,618
[Nicky] Well, it's a harrowing experience
you've been through.

199
00:09:57,701 --> 00:09:59,244
I just think, yeah, well…

200
00:09:59,328 --> 00:10:00,912
I think we keep it light.

201
00:10:00,996 --> 00:10:02,372
Light and bright, Mary.

202
00:10:02,456 --> 00:10:03,957
-[raises volume]
-[Nicky] Of course!

203
00:10:04,041 --> 00:10:06,960
No, I-- And I… I think… Of course.

204
00:10:07,461 --> 00:10:10,255
And I think you can tell that story
just without all the sens--

205
00:10:10,339 --> 00:10:12,841
Without all the sensory details, you know?

206
00:10:12,924 --> 00:10:15,260
What are we…? Turn this off, please.

207
00:10:15,344 --> 00:10:17,012
[engine revving]

208
00:10:17,095 --> 00:10:18,263
[gravel crunching]

209
00:10:18,347 --> 00:10:19,640
[Turkish music continues]

210
00:10:19,723 --> 00:10:20,724
[brakes grinding]

211
00:10:22,267 --> 00:10:23,477
[car door opens]

212
00:10:24,853 --> 00:10:26,188
[Morgan clears throat]

213
00:10:27,105 --> 00:10:28,273
[car door closes]

214
00:10:29,191 --> 00:10:30,233
[engine running]

215
00:10:30,317 --> 00:10:32,694
Okay, so should we wait for you here?

216
00:10:32,778 --> 00:10:35,530
I need to go pick up a trailer.
I don't need a babysitter for that.

217
00:10:36,448 --> 00:10:38,408
-Okay.
-Lot 21, three bulls.

218
00:10:38,909 --> 00:10:39,743
Go.

219
00:10:39,826 --> 00:10:41,078
[cattle bellowing]

220
00:10:41,870 --> 00:10:43,288
[Morgan sighs loudly]

221
00:10:43,372 --> 00:10:44,956
[engine revving]

222
00:10:46,541 --> 00:10:50,212
-[Nicky] What did you do to him?
-Nothing. He's been in a mood all day.

223
00:10:50,796 --> 00:10:53,006
So are these the papers
for the registration?

224
00:10:53,090 --> 00:10:54,424
Oh. Yeah, I got it.

225
00:10:54,966 --> 00:10:56,051
[cattle bellowing]

226
00:10:56,134 --> 00:10:58,220
I can register for an auction, Morgan.

227
00:10:58,303 --> 00:11:00,514
I… I know, I get that.
I'm just, I'm gonna do it, okay?

228
00:11:00,597 --> 00:11:01,556
Why? Why?

229
00:11:01,640 --> 00:11:04,643
You're being so weird.
You've been micromanaging everyone.

230
00:11:04,726 --> 00:11:06,311
-[dog barking]
-[Morgan sighs]

231
00:11:06,937 --> 00:11:09,064
Technically, I am in charge of this job.

232
00:11:10,524 --> 00:11:11,566
What?

233
00:11:12,234 --> 00:11:13,151
Yeah.

234
00:11:13,652 --> 00:11:17,114
Ivan wanted me to do this alone,
but I invited you because…

235
00:11:17,197 --> 00:11:21,034
[inhales] Because I actually…
I don't feel safe alone with Yusuf.

236
00:11:21,118 --> 00:11:25,163
Oh, Ivan wanted you to do this alone?
That's… What did he say?

237
00:11:25,247 --> 00:11:27,290
Nothing. Nothing.
I just, I think he thinks

238
00:11:27,374 --> 00:11:29,334
I'm, like, more assertive in the field.

239
00:11:29,418 --> 00:11:31,002
-[Nicky] In the field?
-Yeah.

240
00:11:31,086 --> 00:11:33,088
So, what, he's not happy
with the job that I'm doing?

241
00:11:33,171 --> 00:11:35,340
That's why I didn't wanna tell you.
You're getting upset.

242
00:11:35,424 --> 00:11:36,883
Of course I'm getting upset!

243
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:40,262
I've compromised my… my time,
my job, my relationship.

244
00:11:40,929 --> 00:11:42,264
What relationship?

245
00:11:42,347 --> 00:11:43,598
[chickens clucking]

246
00:11:43,682 --> 00:11:45,892
-With G-- Jesus.
-Fine.

247
00:11:45,976 --> 00:11:48,145
[clears throat] What brings you
to this cattle auction?

248
00:11:48,228 --> 00:11:50,063
What is your purpose
for acquiring this cattle?

249
00:11:50,147 --> 00:11:51,440
What are you doing?

250
00:11:51,523 --> 00:11:55,110
Um, well, for me, I am a tradwife
with a substantial Instagram following.

251
00:11:55,193 --> 00:11:58,113
I'm here to get some dairy cows to make
my own butter. See what I'm saying?

252
00:11:58,196 --> 00:12:01,074
These are forged documents, Nicky.
You gotta have your backstory straight.

253
00:12:01,658 --> 00:12:05,954
It's a cattle auction, not some New York
Film Academy acting workshop, okay?

254
00:12:06,037 --> 00:12:06,997
Wow, okay, wow.

255
00:12:07,080 --> 00:12:09,750
-[loud thud]
-Fuck, man, watch where you're going.

256
00:12:09,833 --> 00:12:12,252
-[rooster crowing]
-[dogs barking]

257
00:12:12,335 --> 00:12:14,171
[chickens clucking]

258
00:12:15,172 --> 00:12:16,298
[Morgan sighs loudly]

259
00:12:16,381 --> 00:12:18,800
-[audience talking indistinctly]
-[cattle mooing]

260
00:12:20,886 --> 00:12:21,928
[Nicky] Uh-huh.

261
00:12:22,763 --> 00:12:24,222
-Uh-huh.
-[Morgan] Okay, okay, lot 21.

262
00:12:24,806 --> 00:12:27,851
-Three Brazilian Brahman bulls.
-[Nicky] What do you mean?

263
00:12:27,934 --> 00:12:29,770
[Morgan] What is up with these Russians?

264
00:12:29,853 --> 00:12:33,398
Well, I… I thought she said
the catering was coming tomorrow at noon.

265
00:12:33,482 --> 00:12:35,358
-[cattle mooing]
-[Morgan clears throat]

266
00:12:35,442 --> 00:12:38,028
Well, can you get there before
and let them into the back kitchen?

267
00:12:38,111 --> 00:12:39,613
I should be there by 11:45.

268
00:12:40,822 --> 00:12:43,200
Yeah, no, I'm doing great, Rose,
thank you for asking.

269
00:12:43,283 --> 00:12:46,745
You're… you're a team player, okay?
I'm gonna see you tomorrow.

270
00:12:46,828 --> 00:12:47,662
Bye.

271
00:12:47,746 --> 00:12:49,498
-[indistinct chatter]
-[man laughing]

272
00:12:49,581 --> 00:12:50,957
[Nicky sighs]

273
00:12:51,041 --> 00:12:52,083
[cattle mooing]

274
00:12:52,167 --> 00:12:53,210
Are we not talking now?

275
00:12:53,293 --> 00:12:55,587
I'm on very thin ice
with the congregation, Morgan.

276
00:12:55,670 --> 00:12:58,715
Okay? So if all I'm doing is
keeping you company, you're a big girl.

277
00:12:58,799 --> 00:13:00,509
You can do this job all by yourself.

278
00:13:01,092 --> 00:13:02,135
[Morgan scoffs]

279
00:13:04,221 --> 00:13:05,472
[door squeaks]

280
00:13:08,642 --> 00:13:09,768
[door slams shut]

281
00:13:12,354 --> 00:13:14,314
Fuck me.

282
00:13:15,065 --> 00:13:16,900
Lot 15, lot 15.

283
00:13:16,983 --> 00:13:20,153
This big, black, beautiful bull
weighs in at 1,082 pounds.

284
00:13:20,237 --> 00:13:22,030
We'll start the bidding at $2.

285
00:13:22,113 --> 00:13:23,990
[speaking rapidly]
Two bidder, lookin' at three.

286
00:13:24,074 --> 00:13:26,952
I got three bidder, lookin' at four.
Four bidder, lookin' at five.

287
00:13:27,035 --> 00:13:29,412
Five bidder, bidder, buy.
Four twenty-five. Lookin' for five.

288
00:13:29,496 --> 00:13:31,748
Lookin' for five.
Five bidder, lookin' at six.

289
00:13:31,832 --> 00:13:34,751
I got six bidder, lookin' for seven.
Six bidder, lookin' at seven.

290
00:13:34,835 --> 00:13:37,295
-I got seven bidder, lookin' for eight…
-[Nicky scoffs]

291
00:13:37,879 --> 00:13:39,506
-[Natalie] Is it nice there?
-[exhales]

292
00:13:39,589 --> 00:13:42,801
Well, you don't always
have to eat at McDonald's. You can…

293
00:13:42,884 --> 00:13:46,221
Oh, yeah, go, go, go.
Okay, love you too. I will.

294
00:13:46,304 --> 00:13:48,765
[inhales deeply] Kevin sends his love.

295
00:13:48,849 --> 00:13:49,891
[Linda] Mm-hmm. [inhales]

296
00:13:49,975 --> 00:13:52,185
Oh, woof, those are gorgeous.

297
00:13:52,269 --> 00:13:54,020
Yes, they are. We have a problem.

298
00:13:54,855 --> 00:13:56,690
Yeah, what's that? [inhales]

299
00:13:57,941 --> 00:14:02,696
-To Mrs. Mayor, you win. XX, Andrei.
-[Linda breathes heavily]

300
00:14:03,196 --> 00:14:04,447
Sorry, who's Andrei?

301
00:14:04,531 --> 00:14:07,158
[inhales] The criminal
that Nicky brought into my home,

302
00:14:07,242 --> 00:14:10,954
a man fresh out of prison
who sat at our dining table

303
00:14:11,037 --> 00:14:13,248
listening to me complain about Tom.

304
00:14:13,832 --> 00:14:16,585
I thought you said
Andrei was a surgeon back home.

305
00:14:16,668 --> 00:14:17,502
Plastic.

306
00:14:18,044 --> 00:14:19,880
The man is fresh out of prison.

307
00:14:19,963 --> 00:14:23,675
He told me that Tom would be exposed,
and now this?

308
00:14:24,801 --> 00:14:26,595
Holy shit, Mom.

309
00:14:26,678 --> 00:14:30,390
Tom Donaldson has very deep pockets.

310
00:14:30,473 --> 00:14:35,312
One quick investigation,
and the breadcrumbs lead directly to me.

311
00:14:35,395 --> 00:14:39,357
-Mm-hmm.
-Andrei is interested in me,

312
00:14:39,983 --> 00:14:41,735
Natalie, romantically.

313
00:14:41,818 --> 00:14:43,153
[Natalie smacks lips] Oh.

314
00:14:43,737 --> 00:14:46,239
Yeah? He, he told you that, or…?

315
00:14:46,323 --> 00:14:48,283
We slept together, Natalie.
I slept with him.

316
00:14:48,366 --> 00:14:50,327
Oh, Mom!

317
00:14:50,410 --> 00:14:51,703
-What?!
-After dinner.

318
00:14:51,786 --> 00:14:52,746
-Mom!
-Twice.

319
00:14:52,829 --> 00:14:55,332
Oh, God. Where was Nicky?

320
00:14:55,415 --> 00:14:57,667
[yells] What has that got to do
with anything?

321
00:14:57,751 --> 00:14:59,336
-Oh!
-The important thing is,

322
00:14:59,419 --> 00:15:01,671
this is not how I want to win this race.

323
00:15:01,755 --> 00:15:04,758
I want the people of this town to elect me

324
00:15:04,841 --> 00:15:06,801
because I'm the right choice,

325
00:15:06,885 --> 00:15:10,972
not force my way in
by kneecapping the competition.

326
00:15:11,056 --> 00:15:13,808
Mm-hmm. So you… you want me
to throw them out?

327
00:15:13,892 --> 00:15:18,480
No, I want you to bring up
one of the good vases from the basement.

328
00:15:18,563 --> 00:15:20,357
-[gate clanking]
-[bull bellows]

329
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:21,733
[auctioneer] Lot 21, lot 21.

330
00:15:21,816 --> 00:15:25,236
We'll start the bidding
for these magnificent animals at $2.

331
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:26,237
Do I hear $2?

332
00:15:26,321 --> 00:15:27,864
Hey, do those look like bulls to you?

333
00:15:28,531 --> 00:15:31,785
I see gigantic testicles.
You're a teacher, you do the math.

334
00:15:31,868 --> 00:15:33,286
[auctioneer speaking indistinctly]

335
00:15:34,537 --> 00:15:36,665
[speaking rapidly]
Seven bidder, lookin' at eight.

336
00:15:36,748 --> 00:15:38,750
-I got eight here…
-Hey, excuse me.

337
00:15:39,376 --> 00:15:42,462
Ten, bidder, eleven.
Eleven here, lookin' at twelve.

338
00:15:42,545 --> 00:15:44,422
And twelve! Lookin' at thirteen.

339
00:15:44,506 --> 00:15:46,383
-Twelve-two-five?
-[Morgan] Excuse me.

340
00:15:46,466 --> 00:15:47,384
Hi.

341
00:15:47,467 --> 00:15:48,843
[auctioneer] Twelve bidder…

342
00:15:48,927 --> 00:15:50,345
Fucking asshole.

343
00:15:50,428 --> 00:15:52,681
Nicky, I need help right now,
right now, okay? [inhales]

344
00:15:52,764 --> 00:15:55,266
Take the ticket.
The auction guy's not looking at me.

345
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:57,435
-Why is he not looking at you?
-Because he's mad at me.

346
00:15:57,519 --> 00:16:00,271
How could the auctioneer
be mad at you, Morgan?

347
00:16:00,355 --> 00:16:03,233
Nicky, please just take the ticket, okay?
You can't lose this, trust me.

348
00:16:03,316 --> 00:16:04,609
What does that mean?

349
00:16:04,693 --> 00:16:05,777
[auctioneer speaking]

350
00:16:05,860 --> 00:16:07,696
[Morgan] Ivan said
he thinks you're a liability.

351
00:16:07,779 --> 00:16:10,573
-I brought you here to prove him wrong.
-What are you saying, liability?

352
00:16:10,657 --> 00:16:13,243
-What are you talking about?
-He's questioning your value.

353
00:16:13,326 --> 00:16:16,746
-Get the cows. Get the cows.
-What the fuck, Morgan? Excuse me!

354
00:16:16,830 --> 00:16:19,207
-[Morgan] Sir!
-This is a person who wants a cow!

355
00:16:19,290 --> 00:16:21,918
-Hello?
-[Nicky] Hello? Sir?

356
00:16:22,002 --> 00:16:24,087
Move! I'm not with her!

357
00:16:24,170 --> 00:16:26,548
-[Nicky] I'm waving the ticket!
-Going once, going twice…

358
00:16:26,631 --> 00:16:27,590
-No, no, no, no!
-What?

359
00:16:27,674 --> 00:16:29,926
-[bang]
-Sold right here at twenty-four!

360
00:16:30,010 --> 00:16:31,553
Fuck! Shit!

361
00:16:31,636 --> 00:16:34,472
Fuck. Sorry. Fuck. Ah!

362
00:16:34,556 --> 00:16:36,182
[suspenseful music playing]

363
00:16:36,266 --> 00:16:37,392
[loud bang]

364
00:16:37,892 --> 00:16:40,770
You had one fucking job. One job.

365
00:16:41,479 --> 00:16:43,857
How hard is it to buy a couple cows?

366
00:16:43,940 --> 00:16:45,942
Okay, well, where were you?

367
00:16:46,026 --> 00:16:48,862
I was getting the fucking trailer
for the fucking cows!

368
00:16:49,446 --> 00:16:53,324
I can't even trust you to buy a cow.
Like, what the fuck is wrong with you?

369
00:16:53,408 --> 00:16:54,325
I… I don't know.

370
00:16:55,952 --> 00:16:57,328
Where are they? Where are they?!

371
00:16:57,412 --> 00:16:59,247
First of all, put that away.

372
00:16:59,330 --> 00:17:00,331
[dog barking]

373
00:17:00,415 --> 00:17:02,042
-Put the gun away.
-Stop.

374
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:04,586
Why are you waving a gun around
in front of a crowd of people

375
00:17:04,669 --> 00:17:06,713
who are also very likely carrying guns?

376
00:17:06,796 --> 00:17:10,508
-Okay, I will do it.
-Nicky, seriously, just let me think.

377
00:17:10,592 --> 00:17:13,803
I'm a pastor, Morgan.
It's what I do. I talk to people, okay?

378
00:17:13,887 --> 00:17:16,598
And up until two weeks ago,
I was very good at my job.

379
00:17:16,681 --> 00:17:19,601
Okay, if you don't get the cows,
I will get the fucking cows.

380
00:17:19,684 --> 00:17:21,978
And I swear to you,
I will kill that entire family, okay?

381
00:17:22,062 --> 00:17:24,064
-Get a grip, come on.
-You are very intense.

382
00:17:24,147 --> 00:17:25,190
-Go get them!
-Stop.

383
00:17:25,273 --> 00:17:26,191
Okay!

384
00:17:26,274 --> 00:17:29,277
[funky music playing]

385
00:17:37,077 --> 00:17:38,036
[music ends]

386
00:17:38,119 --> 00:17:39,079
Excuse me.

387
00:17:39,621 --> 00:17:44,375
Just, uh, wanted to congratulate you
on the bulls you won today.

388
00:17:44,918 --> 00:17:46,127
Thank you very much.

389
00:17:46,211 --> 00:17:50,340
Yeah, you know,
I, uh, came here today with one goal,

390
00:17:50,423 --> 00:17:53,176
and that was to win those exact bulls.

391
00:17:53,259 --> 00:17:56,387
But I was not able to do it,
and you were, so…

392
00:17:56,888 --> 00:17:58,431
-There's always next time.
-Yeah.

393
00:17:58,515 --> 00:18:03,019
I have a large, um, bag of money
that I would happily hand over to you

394
00:18:03,103 --> 00:18:05,939
if that were to make any kind of…
[gulps, smacks lips]

395
00:18:06,022 --> 00:18:07,065
…difference.

396
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:10,360
No outside trading.

397
00:18:11,236 --> 00:18:13,404
-You trying to dodge the rules?
-No, no.

398
00:18:13,488 --> 00:18:17,033
I just… I just didn't know
whether a… a large duffel bag of cash

399
00:18:17,117 --> 00:18:19,744
would… would maybe help you in any way.

400
00:18:19,828 --> 00:18:23,039
-Bill, truck's ready to load. We gotta go.
-[cattle mooing]

401
00:18:23,123 --> 00:18:24,624
I got enough money.

402
00:18:24,707 --> 00:18:26,084
-We gotta go.
-[Nicky] Okay.

403
00:18:26,918 --> 00:18:31,297
Hey, between you and me,
you're lucky I'm a God-fearing Christian.

404
00:18:31,798 --> 00:18:34,425
There's some other people around here
who would be less forgiving.

405
00:18:35,802 --> 00:18:38,263
I agree completely.
As a member of the clergy,

406
00:18:39,305 --> 00:18:43,059
I… I just want to be clear,
I'm not here to break any rules.

407
00:18:43,143 --> 00:18:45,061
I've never been
to a cattle auction before.

408
00:18:45,145 --> 00:18:47,021
-You're so young for a pastor.
-[chuckles] Yeah.

409
00:18:47,105 --> 00:18:48,231
Thank you. Um…

410
00:18:48,314 --> 00:18:52,819
You know, my congregation
wanted to buy these bulls

411
00:18:52,902 --> 00:18:55,196
for a fa-- farmer that, that, um…

412
00:18:55,989 --> 00:19:00,034
that's struggling
with hoof-and-mouth disease.

413
00:19:00,118 --> 00:19:05,165
The whole flock just decimated,
so everyone wanted to pitch in to help,

414
00:19:05,248 --> 00:19:08,042
but I… I don't want to trouble you
any more than I already have.

415
00:19:08,126 --> 00:19:09,669
I'm so sorry. Please send our prayers.

416
00:19:09,752 --> 00:19:11,504
Thank you so much.
I will send your prayers.

417
00:19:11,588 --> 00:19:13,423
His parents were decapitated.

418
00:19:13,506 --> 00:19:14,424
[cattle bellowing]

419
00:19:14,507 --> 00:19:17,677
Yeah, in an accident.
Seatbelt just… [mimicking]

420
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:20,221
And then charred to a crisp.

421
00:19:20,305 --> 00:19:23,016
So that was…
that's been hard for all of us.

422
00:19:23,683 --> 00:19:24,559
So…

423
00:19:25,518 --> 00:19:28,062
Anyway, I… I'll leave you be.

424
00:19:29,439 --> 00:19:30,815
-[Bill] Pastor?
-Yeah?

425
00:19:32,275 --> 00:19:34,319
We can't sell you these bulls.

426
00:19:36,070 --> 00:19:37,155
I understand.

427
00:19:37,655 --> 00:19:40,950
[Bill] We could never take money
from the church. Please.

428
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:43,578
Let us gift them to you.

429
00:19:44,162 --> 00:19:46,873
Oh, no. No, no, no.
These are tens of thousands of dollars.

430
00:19:46,956 --> 00:19:49,417
Like, I couldn't. My conscience
honestly could not take that.

431
00:19:49,500 --> 00:19:50,710
-[Bill] I insist.
-No, I'm se…

432
00:19:50,793 --> 00:19:52,587
-Please, just take the money.
-[Bill] Pastor.

433
00:19:52,670 --> 00:19:54,505
Just take half of it. Keep the bag.

434
00:19:54,589 --> 00:19:57,550
Pastor, pastor.
This is the congregation's money.

435
00:19:59,052 --> 00:20:02,972
I mean, "Whoever knows
the right thing to do and fails to do it…

436
00:20:03,806 --> 00:20:05,642
-…for him it is a sin."
-[woman] Mm-hmm.

437
00:20:07,060 --> 00:20:09,479
Yeah, it's James 4:17.

438
00:20:09,562 --> 00:20:10,647
[woman chuckling]

439
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:12,523
-It's an important one.
-[Bill] It is.

440
00:20:13,149 --> 00:20:14,692
[funky music playing]

441
00:20:18,112 --> 00:20:19,239
[music ends]

442
00:20:19,322 --> 00:20:21,449
-What is this?
-You can pick them up in the morning.

443
00:20:21,532 --> 00:20:25,119
I'll be on the first train out to comfort
a woman who just lost both her parents.

444
00:20:25,203 --> 00:20:27,580
[Yusuf] What the fuck?
They just gave it to you?

445
00:20:28,164 --> 00:20:28,998
Yeah.

446
00:20:30,959 --> 00:20:32,418
[paper rustling]

447
00:20:32,502 --> 00:20:34,462
[softly] That's… No, that's terrible.

448
00:20:34,545 --> 00:20:35,672
[inhales deeply]

449
00:20:35,755 --> 00:20:37,298
-Oh my God. Nah.
-[doorbell ringing]

450
00:20:37,382 --> 00:20:38,800
[door squeaking]

451
00:20:40,343 --> 00:20:43,012
Oh my God. [exhales]

452
00:20:46,599 --> 00:20:48,184
-Hey, Linda.
-Hi. [chuckles]

453
00:20:48,268 --> 00:20:50,937
-Hope I'm not interrupting anything.
-No, not at all.

454
00:20:51,020 --> 00:20:52,855
-Come on in.
-Thanks.

455
00:20:52,939 --> 00:20:55,566
-[insects chirping]
-[door squeaking]

456
00:20:55,650 --> 00:20:59,570
I mean, I honestly thought I knew
who this man was.

457
00:20:59,654 --> 00:21:01,614
-Linda, I saw the pictures.
-[gasps]

458
00:21:01,698 --> 00:21:06,494
No. No one should ever have to see
that oily beast in a G-string.

459
00:21:06,577 --> 00:21:07,912
I'll take your word for it.

460
00:21:07,996 --> 00:21:10,707
I want you to know
that I feel sick about this.

461
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:12,750
-I really do.
-Well, there's really no need.

462
00:21:12,834 --> 00:21:14,627
No, no, no, there is. There is a need.

463
00:21:14,711 --> 00:21:17,422
Usually at work
I'm the only woman in the room,

464
00:21:18,006 --> 00:21:21,301
and I've developed
quite an impressive bullshit detector.

465
00:21:21,384 --> 00:21:23,970
Well, don't beat yourself up
about it. [laughs]

466
00:21:24,053 --> 00:21:26,597
I've rescinded my endorsement of that man.

467
00:21:26,681 --> 00:21:29,058
-Publicly and financially.
-Hmm.

468
00:21:29,767 --> 00:21:31,769
[Annette inhales] And…

469
00:21:34,522 --> 00:21:36,065
I want you to have this.

470
00:21:37,358 --> 00:21:38,401
[clicks tongue]

471
00:21:38,484 --> 00:21:40,695
There's power in numbers, Linda.

472
00:21:41,195 --> 00:21:44,490
You've done nothing wrong here.
You've run a clean and honest campaign.

473
00:21:44,574 --> 00:21:48,494
Well, no campaign is fully clean.

474
00:21:48,578 --> 00:21:49,996
Annette, I couldn't possibly.

475
00:21:50,079 --> 00:21:54,417
Consider this my way of getting
all that oil off my guilty conscience.

476
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:55,460
[laughs nervously]

477
00:21:56,294 --> 00:22:00,798
I want to back a campaign
that I can be proud of.

478
